related_questions.question: Is relish just pickles?
related_questions.snippet: The word “relish” can refer to a wide variety of condiments including chow-chow, hot relish, and chutney, but in the United States, it almost always refers to pickle relish. Pickle relish is a jam-like condiment made from either pickled cucumbers or fresh cucumbers seasoned with vinegar, sugar, salt, and spices.

buttons.subtitle: What Does Relish Taste Like?
buttons.title: The Best Pickle Relish | Taste Test - Serious Eats
buttons.snippet: A good relish should have crunchy, fresh-tasting chunks of cucumbers. Relishes that were mushy or tasted like cucumber skins did not score highly. The flavors should be bright and bold—this is a condiment, after all—with a good balance between sweet and tart.
